					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This reminds me of my own problems with my Sonic 3 cartridge I've had since 1994. It never saved games, but I didn't consider this a major issue as a kid. Only recently I got curious about it again and decided to check what could be the problem, and to my surprise, the FRAM appeared to have been intentionally disabled, as one of the traces leading to it was cut.<br /><br />I have no idea why anyone would do that, specially considering this was an original TecToy cartridge, bought sealed from a respectable store.<br /><br />I haven't tried to restore that trace yet, but I guess it would be cool if my cartridge was finally able to save.</div>

