			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Use diode test and measure each IO against VCC and GND, they should all show very similar results. If one differs from the rest then that pin may be fucked. I revived a SoR2 cart by placing a pullup resistor on a pin that didn't match the others.<br /><br />Sonic 3 will boot without any of its companion hardware present provided you wire !CE and !OE pins to the ROM properly. If this most bare config doesn't work then it narrows the problem down to PCB and ROM. If all traces reach the ROM from cart edge you have a bad ROM at your hand. The PCB uses crappy glue vias that may fail in some way.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tmeeco.eu">http://www.tmeeco.eu</a><!-- m --></div>
